stories.body: I told my girlfriend she drew her eyebrows too high. She seemed surprised!
stories.author: Ian Malcolm

stories.body: My wife told me I had to stop acting like a flamingo. So I had to put my foot down!
stories.author: Alan Grant

stories.body: So a vowel saves another vowel’s life. The other vowel says, “Aye E! I owe you!”
stories.author: John Hammond

stories.body: Two goldfish are in a tank. One says to the other, “Do you know how to drive this thing?”
stories.author: A Unix System

stories.body: I am become Death, the destroyer of worlds.
stories.author: J. Robert Oppenheimer
